<br>
As an aside, and not totally off-topic;  I only see a handful of active participants on this board, and many of those were in opposition to anything Shintou said (I'm aware that's an over generalization).  It seems that if Shintou could have set aside some of his ego and placated his opponents with a bit more docility, he may have been able to state his case for a longer period, but the result would have probably been the same.  I didn't see anyone being overly rational in the several debates involved (another over-generalization). <br>
<br>
Things don't often go smoothly when fanatics are involved, and it seemed several diametrically opposed perspectives came into conflict.  It was sad, and discouraged me from becoming a bit more active.  Especially when I come to play a game.  If I can't play the game the way I want, I move on, either in-game or too another.  If FV doesn't pan out, then I'll be in another game.  Hopefully one I enjoy will be released soon.  As it is, EQ is the only one of this genre I still desire to play.  <br>
<br>
I do hope more objective moderation becomes a norm for this board. Since I don't feel part of &quot;the crowd&quot;, and will probably not be extremely active here -- it would be nice to feel comfortable posting here once in awhile.  As it is, I almost feel as if I'm intruding on a private playground.  <br>
<br>
Okay, to close this lengthy post and try to swing back towards the topic -- what was it, btw?  Oh, I think both sides of the numerous discussion behaved poorly, and it wouldn't have been so lengthy and troublesome had more moderation been present, or moved to a more appropriate location.  There would be no discussion of whether or not someone was a martyr, how poorly they were treated, etc.<br>
